# shellcheck shell=bash

# Provider configuration parsing, credential resolution, and input
# scrubbing for rotation providers.
#
# Provides three public functions:
#   bwx-scrub-config-value   — reject shell expansion characters
#   bwx-resolve-credential   — resolve credential references (BWS, file, env)
#   bwx-provider-config      — typed config field extraction from note text
#
# All provider config values pass through bwx-scrub-config-value before
# reaching provider code. Credential values (resolved secret content)
# skip the scrub since they may legitimately contain any byte.

